<br>
Like Stormtower mentioned on Prexus, there was a LOT of friction in the alliance.  For whatever reason, people couldn't seem to get along or make compromises on even minor issues - there was squabbling about everything from when the meetings would occur, to every rule that discussed, to accusations flying around whether the larger guild and my friend was just trying to absorb smaller guilds and destroy their rules and &quot;families&quot; (they weren't).  With no alliance leader, decisions were rarely made and when they were people would threaten to pull their guild out of the alliance.  <br>
<br>
When the raids did occur, they were disasters for the most part - people felt slighted on the signups, and even with loot rules in place nobody could decide who would get the loot (no OUR ranger deserves that Thorny Vine tunic!!  Why is it that YOUR guild always gets loot?), raid leadership was notibly absent and they almost always ended up in mass wipeouts with insanely long CR times.<br>
<br>
In contrast, the guild I was in had about 25+ low to mid 50s, and we were not aligned with the United Guilds of Drinal.  My guild leader instead focused on building alignments with other like-minded guilds. We ran successful raids and had a lot of fun with our aligned guilds, with no bad blood, no loot arguments, and no hassle.  I think having alliances with like-minded guilds rather than trying to put a bunch of dissimilar guilds in one alliance works a LOT better.  And even as a member of a guild, by getting out and getting to know other guilds, you can help forge these alliances. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unimiane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nimiane</A> at: 1/3/02 5:06:41 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  